column5: It was a great day out there for my first time out. Was fishing with Governator and friend. Nice to make the acquaintances. No white stripe for us. Too bad the whitie grounds were just a bit too far for this body Good to see a number of good folk again. Even better to meet many for the first time. My mother's happy too. We brought home enough perch for her and a couple of church friends to have a perch lunch this week.  More brownie points for me
Great pics Joey glad to see so many people out for teh day again.

Great Pic's and Report Joey... It was so good to see you and Paul again, as many other OFC'rs... and meet some new one's too.. My grandson's had a blast too..  Now, FINALLY a female to win the tourny..  WTG Joey...Congrats
Joey wins everything.
She does not  I've never even come close to the Lakair trophy, so now that you said that, I'll have to win it this year
Didn't Ron's daughter win it the 3rd year???
Lucky duck
Looks like a GREAT turnout! I sure did miss a fun day. Congrats to you Joey!!!!!

Great pictures Joey, I feel bad I never go to these events that OFC hosts. When I can start driving this upcoming years end I'll be attending events and getting to know EVERYBODY!  Thanks for sharing!
Looks like everyone had a great time, smiles everywhere. Congratulations on the biggest fish Joey.
A couple of pics from fishing with Governator.
Congrats on the win again Joey!  Nice to see you and Paul with a bunch of nice fish.  Tony
I had a lot of fun fishing with you guys (Regardless of my result lol).  Thanks for the advice on switching my jig... too bad I started getting bites at the end of the day haha.
congrats joey nice fish
Lots of happy faces getting together for a good cause. Great photos!
Thanks for the report Joey and congrats!! Very nice pics and loved the video, memories for a lifetime there.
very nice pictures joey, it was a great event, nice to meet a bunch of ofners in person, congrats on the laker, good laughs with everyone aswell, look forward to the event next year
I think I'm gonna have to have nametags next year for OFC'rs, I missed talking to SO MANY PEOPLE.. or maybe you were all avoiding me.
Forgive my ignorance,but whos this?

Unless I'm going blind (and I could be) it's HTHM.  I have been enjoying all the pictures and reports and I promise next year I'll be there.  Hell if TJ can do it, I can do it.  But what I really want to know is who the hell is this skinny dude?
Yep, Spiel has it right, it is Albert, our HomeTownHandyman.
Ya 30 pounds lighter, then when you seen me last bud.
Make mine holdfast.

Thought I'd start a new Tyler thread as I have lots of pictures (the boss told me to take lots LOL)!  Wow, what a blast today was.  After many, many years of attending this fine fundraiser, I actually won biggest fish this year        What a great turnout this year turned out to be.  So many people I haven't seen in awhile and lots of new people I met.  Really nice seeing all of you today!!  Paul and I joined Terry and Lloyd at our usual haunt and that was a good decision.  Lloyd's stepdaughter thought so too.  Here is a video of her and her big laker  Love the coaching going on by Lloyd!!    There's so many pics, I'm just going to post them with no comment.  Enjoy!  Oh, and Paul actually caught fish                                                Joey
Thanks for the pics and vid. you made her day even better. See you sat in Temagami.
Yup, I'll see you Saturday (what, you not fishing tomorrow?)   I'll send you the video and high res pics to your email Lloyd!

Nope going to get my stuff all packed and fine tuned for 9 days on Temagami. It was so nice to see so many people out today. Its nice to see so many people helping out for a great cause. Hope everyone had as much fun as I did.
great photos Joey  see you next week  Paul too
That's not much bigger than mine
Nice photos and fish!!  Looks like it was a blast
Very nice pics Joey,Thanx.Hard to recognize lots of y'all with all yer clothes on. Joe
Looks like y'all had fun
TJ is furry either way.
Awesome pics joey It was nice to finally meet you guys in person
Looks fun!
I don't know why but pics 4 and 5 look like the fish was cropped in.
I was thinking the same lOL... it's just the snow stuck to it.
Wpow!!  Congrats!!!  Looks lile a great turn out, wish Ii could have made it. Great work by everyone involved!
Excellent pics, had a fun time,  now for the long wait until next year.  I don't think the weather could have been much better either.
Looks like a great time out, wish I wasn't at work all day like a sucker  congrats on your big fish and thanks for the report!
Sounds like a great day for all involved and congrats on winning the Big Fish contest Joey
Wow! It really is getting bigger every year! Congrats to everyone involved in one way or another. Super pics, report and win, Joey!
Great pics J. Great day for sure.

Yes it was a great day,and nice pictures Joey. I was nice to meet the OFC'ers in person instead of behind the PC. Finally got to meet Loyd, Chris K, and me udder brudder Brian. And can't forget the main man, TJ, because of him this would have never happened.
It was a great time. I had a ton of fun fishing. Congratualations to Joey. This was my second time at the event I hope to be there next year and for many years to come...
Congrats on your Win Joey@!!  Great seeing everyone out there again. This was my 7th outing and I think the biggest yet.  see you all next year!!
WOW Joey.... you weren't kidding when you posted *Pic Heavy* Sounds like fun was had by everyone Congrats on the win   and thanks for sharing!!! Leechman
